lenders.loan_because:
I have spent last year designing a GREAT web site between craigslist and facebook with many features. It  is 4 times larger. 10 times safer for the consumer. The site is VERY consumer friendly with many areas, based on giving forward as well.

The site does not have to be a #1 site to succeed, however I have a niche I am 100 certain after 2 yrs of marketing that it could very well be among the top 100. Sometimes, you just know you have a home run! 
I have not put this much into it to stay local.

I need $ 3.834 altogether for phase 1 to finish database, basic first marketing, and a $834 left in legal fees. The balance of site will be out-source in several parts for sites protection.  It can not be launched outside these needs.  

Advertising funds will pay back loan once launched in payments.  I will hire someone on commission to go out locally in advertising sales once up,with someone in sales who wants such job in pocket. Along with calling on national accounts myself from home with a special grand fathered promotion to pay loan back, however site phase 1 must be up and running for such
.

It has not been easy, however I WILL SUCCEED. Please consider my small business loan to get me off the ground.  You will not regret it. I have worked so so hard, sometimes 12 hours a day, sometimes all night from my desktop this last year 1/2. I just need a chance for start up capital to do what I can not do myself. 

Thank You
lenders.occupational_info:
I am a widow. I have  2 sons. I have to work from home. I became disabled some time back with an auto immune disorder called Connective Tissue, which I have lived with for last several years. It actually makes me more dedicated and focused for success. Due to such I am starting over with not enough credit to just go to bank for my needs. I need entrepreneurs & those who can see my vision, believe in me, take a chance on me & give me and my family, along with this business a chance to succeed. 

I must work from home and later work around my disabilities .I am moble just not as much as most in busy lifestyles.  I have no wheel chairs or chains. In my own world I can function fine. I thought I should mention this. Many others who have disabilities have taken dreams and with the right tools have been very success setting up their business around their issues so they are not issues. I can as well, especially since we have the technology to do just that!  

I have raised 2 sons as a widow & I might add "without disability income".  It has not been easy. Yet my older maintains a 4.2.   I am great with budgets, living on less than most families do in american due to such and did so because I am very driven in self motivation. It just seems very hard to get my feet wet with nothing leftover every month in this economy. If i could go out and get a normal job, I have no doubt I could achieve that in no time. But I must work from home. And my business is here. I have put so much in it. I am now at a level where I must have funding to go any further.. 

 I used to be a broker with my own biz prior to getting sick. I gave 15 years to Jaycees. Chaired or assisted in hundreds of local projects from womens shelters to selling jelly...  Work with hospital to women's round table. Collected toys to giving homeless a place to stay. A few years ago I moved to florida for my health.
I am very capable of starting something and then watching & helping team management to it's real potential.  Those with disabilities have 25% higher success rate due to focus and that self motivation to succeed.

I am hoping those good deeds will now come back my way to help complete all my hard work and dreams.
